items.title: Stopping the Greatest Threat to the Amazon, One Fire at a Time
items.description: After four decades of research, a scientist returns to the Amazon in an effort to change the behavior that has led to years of environmental crisis.

items.title: 3 Children Are Injured in Grizzly Bear Attack in British Columbia
items.description: The children were among 11 people who were hurt when a grizzly attacked a school group in a remote part of British Columbia, the authorities said.

items.title: After Russian Strike on Apartment Buildings, Ukraine’s Hope for Survivors Fades
items.description: Russian missiles hit apartment buildings in Ternopil this week, far from the war’s front line. Dozens of civilians, including children, were killed.
